/*Write a method that obtains two non-negative integers and finds their average. 
The average is also an integer, rounded down if necessary. 
The method returns a word in the format: 
Average of A and B is C Where A and B are the values of the first and second arguments, respectively, C is the average.*/

public class Exercise {
    
    public static String average(int a, int b) {
        int c = (a + b) / 2;
        return "Average of " + a + " and " + b + " is " + c;
    }
}
